node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
@realbusinessowners have both built multiple businesses to 7 and 8-figures starting from absolutely nothing. They're now here to give you guys the No-BS tactics and tips that they've learned along the way. 🔥🔥
Follow @realbusinessowners for more. 🔥🔥

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners Here are 10 lessons we learned being in business over the past 13 years...'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 1. Most progress will be made during difficult times 2. You will get screwed over, it's apart of the game.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 3. Entrepreneurship is self development disguised as business. 4. Making money is easy, keeping it is the hard part.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 5. You'll never be satisfied by the end result, enjoy the journey. 6. Building a business isn't that glamorous, just a ton of work.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 7. Once you can afforo afford the Lambo, it isn't that cool. 8. Uncertainty is the barrier of entry to success.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners 9. Always focus on solutions, never the problem. 10. Discipline will take you further than motivation ever will.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners There are no "shortcuts" in business, only obstacles to overcome. We've built several businesses to a combined $13MM/ year in revenue over the past 13 13 years. None of choss businesses have been "easy".'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Real Business Owners @realbizowners If you want no-bullshit content centered around business and what we've learned while building multiple businesses, Follow us, and never hesitate to reach out if you need help.'.

node.text:
This is a rough break down of how millionaires and billionaires use paintings to avoid taxes.

Credit to: @jaketran.io 
Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 4 people and text that says 'BusinessEquity THE HARDER YOU WORK THE MORE TAXES You'll pay. The harder your money works, the less taxes you'll pay. This is one of the main reason how Warren Buffett's tax rate is 17 while the average American's rate is 24%'.

node.text:
When your money is working for you you are getting paid in capital gains, dividends, etc...

This is how the rich make money. When you do this your tax rate is far lower because investments and assets are taxed at a lower rate than wages.

This means the average American pays a higher percent of taxes than the average millionaire. This is why we always stress to get money and buy assets!

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
These numbers are all examples...but as you can see the earlier you start, and longer you continue, the more you're going to end up with.

But age really doesn't matter. Putting your money to work at the age of 60 is better than never putting a penny to work for you in your life!

Follow us @businessequity
